# Appendix O — SLAT for the playground

The playground is where kids and casual users write their first
Motoi Scheme. This appendix covers the safe subset — the SLAT
primitives + composition types + gates that keep the playground
playful and safe.

## The safe verb subset

Playground carts can only call verbs marked `:playground #t`.

```motoi-scheme
(register-primitive
  :name       'draw-circle
  :playground #t             ; safe for the playground
  :signature  \"(draw-circle x y radius) -> void\"
  :body       (lambda (args) ...))

(register-primitive
  :name       'send-money
  :playground #f             ; NOT safe — money verbs never
  :signature  \"(send-money to amount) -> receipt\"
  :body       (lambda (args) ...))
```

The playground gate refuses any verb without `:playground #t`.

## Playground SLAT record

```motoi-scheme
(playground-cart
  :author   'kid-nova
  :age      9
  :cart-id  \"pg-2026-07-12-nova-flowers\"
  :verbs    ((make-canvas 400 400)
             (draw-flower 200 200 :petals 8 :color 'pink)
             (draw-flower 100 300 :petals 6 :color 'yellow)
             (animate :from-frame 0 :to-frame 60))
  :remix-of nil                    ; original work
  :share    'public)
```

Head: `playground-cart`. All fields age-appropriate.

## Playground reference book

There's a small reference for the playground — subset of the full
reference, plainer prose, more pictures, less jargon.

Every playground primitive gets:
- one-line explanation (kid-parsable)
- one worked example (small, complete, runs standalone)
- one visual hint (small illustration or animated gif)

## Playground safety

- No verbs that touch money, inventory, or personal-data surfaces.
- No verbs that call external APIs.
- No verbs that write to persistent storage outside the playground
  sandbox.
- Fuel budget hard-capped low so runaway carts halt fast.

## Sharing playground carts

```motoi-scheme
(playground-share
  :cart-id  \"pg-2026-07-12-nova-flowers\"
  :audience 'family
  :ttl      '30-days
  :comments 'off)              ; comments off by default for kids
```

Kids share with family; family opens a link that renders the cart in
a safe surface. No comments unless a parent turns them on. Priya
audits playground surfaces separately.

